<title>ITALY: Ciampi says no secret deals to bar Italy from EMU.</title>
<headline>Ciampi says no secret deals to bar Italy from EMU.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Treasury Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi said on Wednesday that there were no &quot;secret deals&quot; to keep Italy out of the first wave of members of Europe's planned single currency.</p>
<p>He was responding to journalists after renewed media reports, including in the respected Italian business newspaper Il Sole 24 Ore, that a purported deal was gaining ground among key European governments to delay Italian entry beyond 1999.</p>
</text>
